DOM(Document Object Model):
1.It is a programming interface in web development that allows us to interact and mamipulate the html documents.
2.When the webpages is loaded, the browser create the DOM of the webpage.
3.When an html file is loaded into the browser . The javascript cannot understand the html document directly.
4.DOM: is basically the representation of same html document but in the form of a tree-like structure composed of objects
5.HTML dom it allows javascript to access and modify all elements in html document.
KeyPoints:
6.Structure:the DOM represents the structure of html document as tree;Each node in a tree represents the elements, an atribute,text
7.Manipulate:using js, you can interact with elements we can modify ,add, remove elements
Change Style:
8.Eventhandling:
9.W3C-World Wide Web Cosortium.
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
</head>
<body>
    
</body>
</html>

In Dom all html elements are defined objects 
Example:
 <style>
        .a{
            color: red;
            text-align: center;
           

        }
        .b{
            color: green;
            text-align: center;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1 class="a">yaswanth</h1>
    <h1 class="a">malli</h1>
    <h1 class="a">ravi</h1>
    <h1 class="a">gani</h1>
    <h1 class="b">nani</h1>
    <h1 class="b">gopi</h1>
    <h1 class="b">anwar</h1>
    <h1 class="b">venky</h1>
    
</body>
Output:
yaswanth
malli
ravi
gani
Nani
gopi
anwar
Venky
